    description: `Each country has its own strengths â€” and weaknesses. The Better Life Index evaluates 11 different life aspects: from jobs and health to environment, education, safety, and community.<br><br>No country is best at everything. Thatâ€™s why we compare â€œprofilesâ€â€”unique patterns across all dimensions of well-being. Compare, for example, the Netherlands and the United States. The Netherlands excels in work-life balance and social support, while the U.S. leads in education and incomeâ€”but falls behind in safety and civic engagement.<br><br>The key insight: top-performing countries arenâ€™t perfectâ€”but balanced. They combine moderate to high values across many dimensions to create a more sustainable satisfaction.`,
